 for the preset\\n    26\\t- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\\n    27\\t- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\\n    28\\t- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\\n    29\\t\\n    30\\tThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\\n    31\\tso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\\n    32\\t\\n    33\\t### Geometry handoff contract\\n    34\\t\\n    35\\tMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\\n    36\\t`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\\n    37\\tfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\\n    38\\t`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\\n    39\\t\\n    40\\tPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\\n    41\\t\\n    42\\t- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\\n    43\\t- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\\n    44\\t- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\\n    45\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\\n    46\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\\n    47\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\\n    48\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\\n    49\\t\\n    50\\t`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\\n    51\\tmaterialization version, meshing-config snapshot, and per-root asset\\n    52\\tstatuses/paths.\\n    53\\t\\n    54\\tCompatibility shim:\\n    55\\t\\n    56\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\\n    57\\t  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\\n    58\\t  sidecar name during migration.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n./agent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-001_Define_a_versioned_geometry_asset_contract_for_multiresolution_morphology_bundles/stdout.jsonl:110:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_65\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Centralized the Milestone 5 geometry bundle contract in [geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/geometry_contract.py#L11). It defines `geometry_bundle.v1`, deterministic per-root paths, asset statuses, and one manifest-writing path that records contract version, dataset/materialization, meshing config snapshot, and per-root bundle records.\\n\\nUpdated [mesh_pipeline.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mesh_pipeline.py#L84), [02_fetch_meshes.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py#L41), and [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py#L48) to use that contract end-to-end. The pipeline now writes and tracks raw mesh, raw skeleton, simplified mesh, surface graph, patch graph, descriptor sidecar, QA sidecar, plus a legacy `_meta.json` shim for compatibility. I also documented the layout in [pipeline_notes.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/pipeline_notes.md#L33) and added regression coverage in [test_geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_geometry_contract.py#L29) and [test_config_paths.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_config_paths.py#L54).\\n\\nVerified with `make test`, `.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_config_paths.PipelineConfigPathIntegrationTest.test_pipeline_scripts_work_from_non_repo_cwd_with_absolute_config_path -v`, and `make validate-manifest`.\"}}\n./flywire_codex/test